!! How to edit a setting

# Click the edit (//pencil//) icon in this tiddler's toolbar.
# Below the body editor (the large textarea showing this WikiText) you'll see the ''field editor'' — a list of rows, one per field. You should see rows for `display-currency`, `tag-name`, `renewal-soon-days`, and `show-canceled-default`.
# Change the ''value'' next to the field you want to update. Do not rename the field itself.
# Click the confirm (//checkmark//) icon to save. The change applies immediately — no wiki restart needed.

!! Verify your change took effect

Open or create any tiddler and paste the transclusion below (replace `tag-name` with whichever field you edited):

```
{{$:/plugins/realaaa/subscription-tracker/config/settings!!tag-name}}
```

The rendered tiddler displays the current field value. If it shows your new value, the edit saved correctly and the `Subscriptions` view will already reflect the change.

!! Field reference

|!Field |!Default |!Purpose |
|`display-currency` |`AUD` |Currency used for the //Monthly// and //Yearly// columns and totals. Must match a key in [[$:/plugins/realaaa/subscription-tracker/config/rates]]. |
|`tag-name` |`subscriptions` |Tag identifying subscription tiddlers. Change this if you want a different tag (e.g. `subscription`, `recurring`); existing tiddlers will need to be re-tagged to match. |
|`renewal-soon-days` |`14` |Days-until-renewal threshold for the red highlight on the //Next renewal// column. |
|`show-canceled-default` |`no` |Whether the status filter starts including Canceled rows (`yes`) or hides them by default (`no`). |

!! Common mistake

Editing values inside the reference ''table above'' changes only the documentation, not the settings — the plugin reads the fields, not the body text. If a setting change appears to have no effect, re-open this tiddler in edit mode and confirm you changed the value in the //field editor// row, not in the table cell.
